> Question in response to question:
>
> Does a non-California 1980 VW Vanagon REQUIRE a Cat converter??



According to federal law, all Busses and Vanagons from 1979 on require a cat
converter in all 50 states (and 1976 on in California).  Of course, actual
enforcement varies tremendously, even by county or individual inspection
station depending on the state.

